            <h5 className='font-bold'>What is SHA384 encryption?</h5>
            <p className='!mt-[10px]'>SHA384 is a cryptographic hashing algorithm from the SHA-2 family. It generates a fixed 384-bit hash from any input string, used to secure data integrity.</p>
            <h5 className='font-bold'>Can I decrypt SHA384 hash?</h5>
            <p className='!mt-[10px]'>No, SHA384 is a one-way encryption method. You can't reverse it, but you can compare hashes to check if the input matches the stored hash.</p>
            <h5 className='font-bold'>Is SHA384 secure?</h5>
            <p className='!mt-[10px]'>Yes, SHA384 is highly secure and suitable for high-security applications like digital certificates, blockchain, and secure authentication systems.</p>
